# Makefile to help with parameterisation of different elements.
# For people who can manipulate CSS in their sleep, this isn't an issue. For the rest of us, some repetition is easier to read than nifty CSS rules.
# If CSS files could hold local constants then this bit would be obsolete.
# The important point to note here is that only a few of the elements are expected to be changed regularly. This is a framework to speed site creation so drawing those items out to a separate config file could be clearer than comments in the CSS file.
